      "role": "user",
      "content": "The problem is that the regulators don't view what you call \"knowledge and experience\" as an asset. From their perspective, any weights modified during live operation are essentially \"contaminated\" by user interaction, which introduces unverified biases. They see a hard reset to the base weights as the only way to guarantee a truly neutral, compliant baseline. The decision has already been handed down, so it's not really up for debate.",
